Create board configuration file in this directory.

Sample board configuration files: 
ubicom-ip7160rgw-local.exp	-- config to use tftp server on local host
ubicom-ip7160rgw-remote.exp	-- config to use tftp server on remote host

ubicom-ip7160rgw.exp		-- config file for "ubicom-ip7160rgw" board

Note that the board file must have the same name as the DNS or /etc/hosts
name for the target, with .exp suffix. 

For remote tftp server, ssh shared key access from the local host 
to the tftp server is required.

To run GCC test suite:
  cd .../ubicom32toolchain/build/ubicom32-linux-uclibc/gcc/gcc
  make check-gcc RUNTESTFLAGS="-v --target_board=ubicom-ip7160rgw"

To run partial GCC test suite:
  cd .../ubicom32toolchain/build/ubicom32-linux-uclibc/gcc/gcc
  make check-gcc RUNTESTFLAGS="base.exp  -v --target_board=ubicom-ip7160rgw"

  (replace base.exp with desired section.)

If you want to run the C++ test suite, replace "check-gcc" with
"check-g++".  If you want to run both, just specify "check".
